          <h3 class="text-center" id="pg1"> Etherpad</h3>
          <br>
          <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-12 col-lg-12">
            <h4>Description</h4>
            <p>
              Etherpad allows you to edit documents collaboratively in real-time, much like a live multi-player editor that runs in your browser. Write articles, press releases, to-do lists, etc. together with your friends, fellow students or colleagues, all working on the same document at the same time.All instances provide access to all data through a well-documented API and supports import/export to many major data exchange formats. And if the built-in feature set isn't enough for you, there's tons of plugins that allow you to customize your instance to suit your needs.
            </p>
            <h4>Administration Guide</h4>
            <p>
              You will find an Admin page at the <b><a target="_blank" href="http://local.mazizone.eu:9001/admin" class="app-link" >local.mazizone.eu:9001/admin</a></b></br>
              <b>User Name :</b> admin</br>
              <b>Password :</b> mazizone
            </p>
            <p>
              In order to change the admin password, in the Admin page select settings and change "mazizone" with your password.
              <pre><code>
              "users": {
                "admin": {
                  "password": "mazizone",
                  "is_admin": true
                },
              }
              </code></pre>
            </p>
            <img src="images/etherpad_doc.png" class="img-responsive center-block" alt="Image for Etherpad Admin Panel">
          </div>
          <div class="voffset9"></div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="tab-pane fade" id="p3">
          <h3 class="text-center" id="pg1"> Nextcloud</h3>
          <br>
          <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-12 col-lg-12">
            <h4>Description</h4>
            <p>
              Nextcloud is a private file sync and share communication server. It is fully open source and you can host it yourself or pay a company to do it for you. That way, you are in control of your photos, your calendar and contact data, your documents and everything else.
            </p>
            <h4>Administration Guide</h4>
            <p>
              You will find an Admin page at <b><a target="_blank" href="http://local.mazizone.eu/nextcloud" class="app-link" >local.mazizone.eu/nextcloud</a></b></br>
              <b>User Name :</b> admin</br>
              <b>Password :</b> mazizone
            </p>
            <img src="images/nextcloud_doc.png" class="img-responsive center-block" alt="Image for Nextcloud Admin Panel" style='padding-bottom: 10px'>
            <p>
              To access your personal settings:</br>
                1. Clicking on admin in the top, right corner of your Nextcloud instance. The Personal Settings Menu opens.
            </p>
            <img src="images/nextcloud_doc2.png" class="img-responsive center-block" alt="Image for Nextcloud Admin Panel 2">
            <p>
              2. Choose Personal from the drop down menu.

              Some of the features you will see include the following:
              <ul>
               <li> Usage and available quota</li>
               <li> Manage your profile picture</li>
               <li> Full name You can make this anything you want, as it is separate from your login name, which is unique and cannot be changed</li>
               <li> Email address</li>
               <li> Lists your Group memberships</li>
               <li> Manage your password</li>
               <li> Choose the language for your Nextcloud interface</li>
               <li> Links to desktop and mobile apps</li>
              </ul>
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="voffset9"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-pane fade" id="p4">
          <h3 class="text-center" id="pg1"> Guest Book</h3>
          <br>
          <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-12 col-lg-12">
            <h4>Description</h4>
            <p>
              The MAZI Guest Book is an open source application that can used in events enabling the audience to share their thoughts, photos, etc.
            </p>
            <img src="images/guestbook_doc.png" class="img-responsive center-block" alt="Image for Nextcloud Admin Panel" style='padding-bottom: 10px'>
            <h4>Administration Guide</h4>
            <p>
              To moderate the content, you go to <b><a target="_blank" href="http://local.mazizone.eu:8081/#admin" class="app-link" >local.mazizone.eu:8081/#admin</a></b></br> (username: <b>admin</b> password: <b>mazizone</b>), where you can delete any submission that is inappropriate.
            </p>
            <p>
               For slideshow <b><a target="_blank" href="http://local.mazizone.eu:8081/#projection" class="app-link" >local.mazizone.eu:8081/#projection</a></b>
            </p>
              <h4>Useful Guidelines</h4>
               <p>You can modify the appearance of the GuestBook</p>
             <ul>
                <li>Tags</li>
                <li>Background Image</li>
                <li>Admin Password</li>
                <li>Message</li>
             </ul>               
              <p>
                First connect to your Raspberry pi. The credentials are:</br> 
                  <pre><code>
                    # ssh pi@local.mazizone.eu
                    password: mazizone                    
                  </code></pre>
                </p>
                 <b>Tags</b>
                 <p> 
                  In order to change tags, open the config.js file, which takes place in this path: /var/www/html/mazi-board/src/www/js/config.js</br> 
                  You can remove or edit a tag as you wish in this code line</br>  
                  <pre><code>
                    tags: ['Artist', 'Activist', 'Male', 'Female', 'Student', 'Professor', 'DSIMaker', 'PolicyMaker']
                  </code></pre>
                </p>
                 <b>Background Image</b>
                 <p>
                  In order to change the background image, save the image you want in the following path: /var/www/html/mazi-board/src/www/images</br>
                  Replace the DSI.jpg of the following code, with the name of your image.</br>
                  You can find the code in the following path: /var/www/html/mazi-board/src/www/js/templates/header_tmpl.html </br>  
                  <pre>
                    <code>
                      &lt;div class="header-bar"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
                      &lt;div class="header-image column"&gt;&lt;img src="images/DSI.jpg"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
                    </code>
                  </pre>
                </p>
                 <b>Admin Password</b> 
                 <p>
                  In order to change the admin password, open the config.js file ,which takes place in this path: /var/www/html/mazi-board/src/node/config.js,</br>
                  and then fill  the <b>authPassword</b> with the password you like. 
                  <pre>
                    <code>
                      /* AUTH DATA */
                        authName: 'admin',
                        authPassword: 'password',
                    </code>
                  </pre>
                 </p>
                 <b>Message</b>
                 <p>
                  In order to change the message, open the submission_input_tmpl.html file , which takes place in this path: /var/www/html/mazi-board/src/www/js/templates/submission_input_tmpl.html,</br> 
                  and then change the message <b>(Click here to join the Guest Book...)</b> with the message you wish to be displayed.
                 </p>
              </p>
